          },
          {
            "kind": "plain",
            "text": "سَأَلَ مُحَمَّدُ بْنُ مُسْلِمٍ أَبَا جَعْفَرٍ عَلَيْهِ اَلسَّلاَمُ:"
          },
          {
            "kind": "plain",
            "text": " عَنِ "
          },
          {
            "kind": "plain",
            "text": "اَلرَّجُلِ يُسَلِّمُ عَلَى اَلْقَوْمِ"
          },
          {
            "kind": "plain",
            "text": " فِي"
          }
        ]
      },
      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/man-la-yahduruhu-al-faqih:1:52:1",
      "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/34/1/52/1063",
      "text": [
        " اَلصَّلاَةِ فَقَالَ «إِذَا سَلَّمَ عَلَيْكَ مُسْلِمٌ وَ أَنْتَ فِي اَلصَّلاَةِ فَسَلِّمْ عَلَيْهِ تَقُولُ اَلسَّلاَمُ عَلَيْكَ وَ أَشِرْ بِإِصْبَعِكَ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.1063 - Muhammad ibn Muslim asked Imam Muhammad ibn Ali Al-Baqir (as) about a person who greets others while in prayer.\nImam (as) said: \"If a Muslim greets you while you are in prayer, respond to him by saying, ‘As-salamu ‘alayka,' and gesture with your finger.\""
        ]
      }
    },
